Understand about Pseudo class in CSS.
   1 Hover (`a:hover`): This state triggers when the user hovers their mouse pointer over a link. 
   2  :first-child - Selects the first child element of its parent. 
   3  :last-child - Selects the last child element of its parent
   4  :nth-child(n) - Selects elements based on their position within a parent element, where "n" is a numeric value. 
   5  :first-of-type - Selects the first element of its type within its parent. 
   6  :last-of-type - Selects the last element of its type within its parent. 
   7  :nth-of-type(n) - Selects elements of a specified type based on their position within a parent. 
